<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Spanish - Gu&#237;a para Localizaci&#243;n de Fallas del Sistema El&#233;ctrico - 3200, 4200, 4300, 4400,
        7300, 7400, 7500, 8500, 8600 - FRONT DRIVE AXLE: SPICER S-9000 - STEER ARM AND KING PIN CAP DISASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="4">
        <title>STEER ARM AND KING PIN CAP DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <para>Use
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0200971">Figure 71</hotlnk>
            as a reference to disassemble the steering arm and king pin cap.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0200971" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g0200971" filename="../figg02/G0200971.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 71. Steering Arm and King Pin Cap</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. Steer Arm Assembly</callout1>
                <callout1>2. Hex Nut</callout1>
                <callout1>3. Stud Adapter</callout1>
                <callout1>4. King Pin</callout1>
                <callout1>5. Shim</callout1>
                <callout1>6. Upper Stud</callout1>
                <callout1>7. Spindle Stud</callout1>
                <callout1>8. Knuckle Assembly</callout1>
                <callout1>9. Lower Stud</callout1>
                <callout1>10. Fitting - Grease</callout1>
                <callout1>11. King Pin Cap</callout1>
                <callout1>12. Set Screw</callout1>
                <callout1>13. Nut</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove steer arm lock nuts and stud adapters (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200972">Figure 72</hotlnk>) (lock nuts and stud adapters must be discarded and
                replaced with new ones). Remove steer arm, king pin assembly and shim pack. Be careful not to damage
                trunnion housing seal. Retain and mark shim pack for re-assembly.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200972" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200972" filename="../figg02/G0200972.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 72. Remove Steer Arm Lock Nuts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove lower king pin cap lock nuts and stud adapters (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200973">Figure 73</hotlnk>) (lock nuts and stud adapters must be discarded and
                replaced with new ones). Retain and mark shim pack for re-assembly. Be careful not to damage trunnion
                housing seal.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200973" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200973" filename="../figg02/G0200973.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 73. Remove King Pin Cap Lock Nuts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Carefully remove knuckle assembly from axle housing trunnion (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200974">Figure 74</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200974" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g0200974" filename="../figg02/G0200974.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 74. Remove Knuckle Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
